CHANGELOG.md:795:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw path layouts (frac-0041): `promptclaw/paths.py` now exposes a frozen `RunPathLayout` plus `ProjectPaths.run_layout()`, `ProjectPaths.ensure_run_layout()`, and `ProjectPaths.path_summary()` so project/run filesystem contracts can produce typed layouts, idempotently prepare run directories, and emit JSON-safe operator summaries. Existing project-level path attributes and `run_*` helper return values are preserved; `ArtifactManager.create_run_layout()` now iterates the canonical run layout while keeping the same on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` structure. Empty run ids fail fast with `ValueError` before layout creation. `tests/test_promptclaw_paths_depth.py` pins helper compatibility, JSON-safe summaries, layout preparation through `ArtifactManager`, run-id rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; config, orchestrator, artifact, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
